```

This should implement the following `Manager` interfaces:

``` go
        // Load an image idempotently into the runtime on a host
        LoadImage(string) error

        // ListContainers returns a list of managed by this container runtime
        ListContainers(string) ([]string, error)
        // KillContainers removes containers based on ID
        KillContainers([]string) error
        // StopContainers stops containers based on ID
        StopContainers([]string) error
```

Need to use runtime-specific code, to load images from path.

Unfortunately the standard only covers pulling from a registry.

This PR started as strictly a removal of StackDriver integration code until we can resolve #3623 and #3178 - but I hated seeing dead, duplicated, and poorly organized code so I went a bit further with it by extracting convenience methods from start.go into exit.go so that all may use it.

This also removes all exit related code from util.go, and introduces 3 new methods for fatally exiting:

```
// Usage outputs a usage error and exits with error code 64
func Usage(format string, a ...interface{})

// WithCode outputs a fatal error message and exits with a supplied error code.
func WithCode(code int, format string, a ...interface{})

// WithError outputs an error and exits.
func WithError(msg string, err error)
```

The exit package also supplies constants based on sysexits which may be passed into WithCode().

When we are ready to rewrite the Stackdriver Error integration with newer API's and service accounts, it should be tied into WithError().
